    <!--Steps for cooking Noodles-->
    <center><h1><p><em>--Steps for cooking Noodles--</em></p></h1></center>
    <ol>
      <li>First boil enough water with a bit of salt and Â½ to 1 teaspoon oil.</li>
      <li>Add the noodles and cook them.</li>
      <li>When the noodles are all dente or just about cooked, strain them in a colander.</li> 
      <li>Then rinse them with fresh water.</li>
      <li>Drain off the extra water.</li>
      <li>Later, you can even add  1 to 2 teaspoons of oil on the cooked noodles.</li>
      <li>Mix the oil gently with the noodles and keep aside.</li>
      <li>Later use the boiled noodles in any stir fried noodle recipe.</li>
    </ol>
